			<title><![CDATA[Wenite secures €1.8 million to power the future of data-driven HR]]></title>
			<category><![CDATA[HRtech]]></category>
			<link>https://tech.eu/2026/04/23/wenite-secures-eur18-million-to-power-the-future-of-data-driven-hr/</link>
			<comments>https://tech.eu/2026/04/23/wenite-secures-eur18-million-to-power-the-future-of-data-driven-hr/#comments</comments>
			<description><![CDATA[Wenite, a Ghent-based HR tech startup,has raised €1.8 million in funding to accelerate its European expansion andstrengthen its position as an infrastructure provider for HR service firms. Theround in...]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span><a href="https://www.wenite.io/" target="_blank">Wenite</a>, a Ghent-based HR tech startup,
has raised €1.8 million in funding to accelerate its European expansion and
strengthen its position as an infrastructure provider for HR service firms. The
round includes €1.2 million in equity financing from <a href="https://www.imecistart.com/" target="_blank">Imec.iStart</a>, and a group of
private investors from the HR sector.</span></p>
<p><span>Across Europe, HR service providers, including
strategic consultants and organisational advisors, play a central role in
supporting companies’ people strategies. Today, around 60 per cent of
organisations rely on such providers. </span></p>
<p><span>Despite this, many companies still
depend on fragmented tools like spreadsheets, documents, and form-based surveys
to manage employee data, track wellbeing, and oversee coaching or development
programmes. As a result, valuable insights remain scattered, limiting
efficiency and making it difficult to scale services or measure impact.</span></p>
<p><span>Founded in 2021 by <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jasper-dezwaef/" target="_blank">Jasper Dezwaef</a>,
<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/emiel-cracco-2689a792/" target="_blank">Emiel Cracco</a>, and <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/rvannieuwenhuijse/" target="_blank">Robin Vannieuwenhuijse</a>, Wenite was created to address these
challenges. The platform provides HR consultants with a unified infrastructure
to manage client relationships and employee data. </span></p>
<p><span>It integrates tools for data
collection, CRM, workflow management, and AI-driven analysis, allowing
consultants to centralise insights and deliver measurable outcomes. Through
client-facing dashboards, end organisations gain visibility into progress and impact,
enabling more data-driven decision-making.</span></p>
<blockquote><p><span>We want to become the backbone for
European HR service providers looking to scale their business and make it
data-driven, </span></p></blockquote>
<p><span>says CEO Jasper Dezwaef.</span></p>
<p><span>Wenite’s approach focuses specifically
on the needs of HR service providers, enabling them to automate processes such
as surveys, reporting, and employee follow-up. By consolidating data into a
continuous, evolving client record, the platform helps consultants improve
efficiency while building longer-term client relationships.</span></p>
<p><span>The investment marks a significant
step in Wenite’s ambition to build a scalable, data-driven foundation for HR
services across Europe, as the company accelerates its commercial expansion,
grows its team, and targets a broader market of approximately 20,000 HR service
providers.</span></p>
]]></content:encoded>
